  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Wave Debt Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By supporting Wave Mobile Money SA (Senegal) and Wave C&#xF4;te d&apos;Ivoire SA, IFC anticipates that the Project will contribute to a larger financial inclusion in countries which record some of the lowest account penetrations globally, by giving customers access to affordable accounts and payment services and allowing them to transact more often due to a simple fee structure and lower transaction costs. Beyond the Project, IFC expects that the investment will contribute to promoting systemic changes in the mobile money markets in Sub-Saharan Africa by allowing Wave Mobile Money group to continue rapidly scaling up its services, which, in turn, will demonstrate to incumbents the viability of a transparent and cheaper pricing structure, pushing them to lower transaction costs and simplify their fee structure.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project consists in a financing package of up to EUR130 million to Wave Mobile Money S.A. (Senegal entity) and Wave C&#xF4;te dIvoire S.A. (the Co-Borrowers), mobile money companies offering cash deposit, withdrawal, money transfer, merchant and bill payments. The Co-Borrowers will use the proceeds of the financing to fund their working capital needs, including the pre-financing of agents and bill payments.</narrative>
  </description>
